<h2>‚ö†Ô∏è Common Reasons for Investment Failure</h2>
<ol>
    <li><strong>Blind Following</strong>: Chasing rising and falling prices, buying at highs.
        <ul>
            <li>Case: Bitcoin frenzy in 2017, many people entered at high prices, then halved.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Only Looking at Themes, Not Fundamentals</strong>:
        <ul>
            <li>Case: Among new energy concept stocks, many small companies had no profits and eventually delisted.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Excessive Use of Leverage</strong>:
        <ul>
            <li>Case: Chinese stock "explosion wave" in 2021, many funds were liquidated due to excessive leverage.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Short-term Speculation</strong>:
        <ul>
            <li>The market is a "voting machine" in the short term and a "weighing machine" in the long term. (Graham's famous saying)</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Ignoring Industry Life Cycle</strong>:
        <ul>
            <li>Case: Kodak was eliminated in the digital camera era.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ol>

